summary: Simon Mitchell, 44, stole a laptop, sat nav and phone from a charity .<n>Donna's Dream House is a charity for terminally ill children based in Blackpool .<n>Mitchell claimed to have celebrity contacts to gain the charity's trust .<n>Charity say he repeatedly let them down and left them picking up the pieces .<n>Mitchell pleaded guilty to two counts of theft at Preston Crown Court .<n>He is due to be sentenced at Preston Crown Court next month .

Arizona, Texas, Montana, Missouri, and Oklahoma are the only five states in America that do not have texting at the wheel bans for all drivers .<n>Researchers from Texas A&M School of Public Health found that hospitalizations from car crashes dropped 7 percent between 2003 and 20010 in the 45 states with texting bans .<n>The greatest benefit was seen in states where texting bans are strictly enforced and where an officer can stop a car just on suspicion the driver breaking the law .

Constable's Beaching A Boat, Brighton was looted by the Nazis .<n>The £1million masterpiece was owned by Baron Ferenc Hatvany, who died in 1958 .<n>Descendants of Hatvany say the Nazis stole the painting and smuggled it out of Hungary .<n>The Government-backed Spoliation Advisory Panel, which rules on disputes over looted art, supported the heirs last year and said the Tate had a ‘moral obligation’ to return the painting .<n>The discovery of the permit in the archives of Budapest’s Museum of Fine Arts is the latest twist in an increasingly fraught dispute .
